<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-22T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94119/690: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-22T16:00:00+09:00">November 22, 1940—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 22—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1181. Reference Chungking’s 578, November 20, 10 a.m., to the
                                Department via Shanghai. The Embassy has learned definitely that the
                                United Press in Tokyo did not send the despatch quoted in
                                Chungking’s telegram under reference and further that the United
                                Press here has not sent any report containing similar
                                information.</p>
                            <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Chungking.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>